quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  21,58,So he broke them into pieces—all except the biggest of them—so that they might come back to it
  21,59,"They said, ‘Whoever has done this to Our gods?! He is indeed a wrongdoer!’"
  21,60,"They said, ‘We heard a young man mentioning them. He is called ‘‘Abraham.’’ ’"
  21,61,"They said, ‘Bring him before the people’s eyes so that they may bear witness [against him].’"
  21,62,"They said, ‘Was it you who did this to our gods, O Abraham?’"
  21,63,"He said, ‘No, it was this biggest one of them who did it! Ask them, if they can speak.’"
  21,64,"Thereat they came to themselves and said [to one another], ‘Indeed it is you who are the wrongdoers!’"
  21,65,"Then they hung their heads. [However, they said,] ‘You certainly know that they cannot speak.’"
  21,66,"He said, ‘Then, do you worship besides Allah that which cannot cause you any benefit or harm"
  21,67,Fie on you and what you worship besides Allah! Do you not exercise your reason?’
  21,68,"They said, ‘Burn him, and help your gods, if you are to do anything!’"
  21,69,"We said, ‘O fire! Be cool and safe for Abraham!’"
  21,70,"They plotted to harm him, but We made them the biggest losers"
  21,71,"We delivered him and Lot toward the land, which We have blessed for all nations"
  21,72,"And We gave him Isaac, and Jacob as well for a grandson, and each of them We made righteous"